keywords:
  - hallucination detection
  - large language models
  - code generation
  - LLM evaluation
  - Google Gemini
  - Cohere
abstract: >-
  A dual-mode evaluation framework for measuring hallucination rates in
  state-of-the-art Large Language Models. Compares Google Gemini 2.5 Flash
  and Cohere Command R7B across 100 test cases spanning Python code
  execution and specialized technical knowledge domains (Polars, SQL,
  Spark, Snowflake). Results demonstrate a 25-percentage-point accuracy
  gap (89% vs 64%) with hallucination rates correlating strongly with
  domain specialization.
